issue.body:

- [X] I searched and no similar issues were found

### Description

For most drop operations (like `dropView`) there is a `ifExists` flag to not error if the View or Procedure does not exist. Currently, this has to be done using a `sql` operation, loosing on some of liquibase advantages.

### Steps To Reproduce

Its a "missing feature" so no steps

### Expected/Desired Behavior

When using `ifExists` in a `dropProcedure` operation
1. It does not error on XSD validation
2. When the changeset is run it will not fail if the specified procedure does not exist
